  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted to rank the relative importance of geometric tolerances on the predicted relative hemolysis index; results indicated that impeller tip clearance and inlet diameter were the dominant drivers. This screening informed factor prioritisation but was treated as an internal engineering exercise and is documented in the project technical record rather than as a formal structured artefact within this credibility package.",
