    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 guidance. Validation results demonstrate RHI predictions within experimental uncertainty at all 5 COU operating points. A screening sensitivity study was conducted as part of the engineering analysis to identify dominant geometric parameters; results supported the decision to focus validation resources on impeller tip clearance and inlet diameter variations. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision that the CFD model adequately predicts worst-case hemolysis conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
